A new monster species of snake measuring up to 20ft-long is slithering into Florida, wildlife experts say.

More than 30 Northern African pythons, also known as rock pythons, have been found in a suburban area west of Miami.

It's feared they could they could invade the area quickly if swift action isn't taken. In a bid to solve the problem, the Florida Fish and Wildlife Conservation Commission has hired an animal control expert to patrol the affected area.

